# Next.js App rules — LoyaltyApp (Reviews & Social Proof)

## Project basics
- Framework: **Next.js** (App Router), **TypeScript** with `strict` enabled.
- This is a unified app: API routes handle all backend logic, pages handle the admin UI and review submission.
- DB: **Postgres** via **Prisma** (`@loyalty/db` workspace package).
- Email: **Postmark** (`@loyalty/email` workspace package).
- Package manager: **pnpm** (workspaces).

## API routes (`apps/web/app/api/`)
- Shopware lifecycle: `/api/app/register`, `/api/app/confirm`, `/api/app/uninstall`
- Webhooks: `/api/webhooks/order`, `/api/webhooks/order-cancelled` — verify HMAC signature before processing.
- Widget: `/api/widget/reviews` — public, CORS-restricted to shop domain, rate-limited.
- Review submission: `/api/review-submission/[token]` — token-authenticated.
- Admin: `/api/admin/*` — authenticated via Shopware iframe handshake.
- Cron: `/api/cron/*` — protected by CRON_SECRET header.
- Health: `/api/health`

## Webhooks & security
- All Shopware webhooks must verify the HMAC-SHA256 signature.
- Webhook handlers must be **idempotent** (dedup by order_id + product_id).
- Store credentials encrypted (AES-256-GCM) using ENCRYPTION_KEY env var.

## Data model
- merchants(shop_id, shop_url, api_key, secret_key, shop_secret, settings_json)
- reviews(merchant_id, product_id, rating, title, body, author_name, author_email, status, merchant_reply)
- review_requests(merchant_id, order_id, product_id, customer_email, token, scheduled_at, status)

## Email scheduling
- Database-driven cron: review_requests with scheduled_at, polled every 5 minutes.
- No Redis/BullMQ — keep it simple for MVP.

## Testing
- Unit tests: Vitest.
- Integration tests: mock Shopware payloads, verify DB writes.

## Observability
- Structured JSON logging via pino.
- Sentry for error tracking.
- Health endpoint at /api/health.

## Dev ergonomics
- Use `APP_URL` env var (ngrok during dev).
- Keep secrets out of repo. Reference `.env.example`.
